          Terraform needs to initialize your project before creating resources.
          Run:
        </p>
        <CodeContainer
          ><pre><code class="language-bash">terraform init
</code></pre></CodeContainer
        >
        <h3 id="step-2-plan-the-terraform-changes">
          Step 2: Plan the Terraform Changes üßæ
        </h3>
        <p>Review what Terraform will do without making changes yet:</p>
        <CodeContainer
          ><pre><code class="language-bash">terraform plan
</code></pre></CodeContainer
        >
        <h3 id="step-3-apply-the-configuration">
          Step 3: Apply the Configuration üí•
        </h3>
        <p>
          Now that everything looks good, apply the configuration to create your
          S3 bucket:
        </p>
        <CodeContainer
          ><pre><code class="language-bash">terraform apply
</code></pre></CodeContainer
        >
        <p>
          Terraform will prompt you to confirm the action. Type <code>yes</code>
          to proceed.
        </p>
        <h2 id="verify-the-s3-bucket">Verify the S3 Bucket üéâ</h2>
        <p>
          After applying the configuration, check the AWS S3 console to verify
          the bucket was created successfully.
        </p>
